  "prompt": "What is a bank branch name?",
  "response": "A bank branch name typically refers to a specific location or office of a bank where customers can conduct various financial transactions and services. Each branch has a unique identifier, often based on its geographic location, which helps distinguish it from other branches within the same bank. For example, a bank might have branches named \"Downtown Branch\" or \"Main Street Branch.\" These names help customers identify the most convenient branch for their needs.",
